  <div class="faq">
    <h3>Does Turnitin detect ChatGPT?</h3>
    <p>Yes, Turnitin can detect raw ChatGPT output with high accuracy. However, AI text that has been properly humanized or significantly edited typically bypasses Turnitin detection.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>What percentage does Turnitin flag as AI?</h3>
    <p>Turnitin shows an AI writing percentage. Scores above 20% are typically flagged for review. Raw ChatGPT output usually scores 80-95%. Properly humanized text typically scores under 10%.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq">
    <h3>Can Turnitin detect Gemini or Claude?</h3>
    <p>Yes. Turnitin's detection covers all major AI writing models including ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and Llama. The detection patterns are similar across all models.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="faq" style="border:none">
    <h3>Does Turnitin save my submissions?</h3>
    <p>Yes. By default, Turnitin stores submitted documents in its database and uses them to check future submissions. Some institutions opt out of this. Check with your institution for their specific settings.</p>
